description:
## Goal
Implement the real Agent struct and its event-loop task. The loop reads one inbound `Block`, appends to history, linearizes, calls the active `ARModel`, translates `ModelStreamEvent`s into `AgentEvent`s on the broadcast channel, appends the resulting `AgentMessage` Block to history, and emits `BlockComplete` + `RunComplete` before returning to await the next inbound Block. Single-task design ⇒ "one pending Model call per Agent" falls out structurally.

## Reference docs
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` §Agent (authoritative)
- `blueprint/pristine-phase1-architecture/plan.md` §"Step 7: Agent event loop", §"`AgentEvent`", §"Agent event loop"
- `STYLE_GUIDE.md`

## Implement in `src/agent.rs`
- `pub struct AgentId` — already defined in `src/history.rs` from Step 2. Re-export via `pub use crate::history::AgentId;` so callers can write `agent::AgentId` if they want.
- `pub struct Agent`:
  - `id: AgentId`
  - `system_prompt: String`
  - `models: HashMap<ModelRole, Arc<dyn ARModel>>`
  - `history: History` (owned; not shared)
  - `inbound: mpsc::Receiver<Block>` (taken by `run`)
  - `outbound: broadcast::Sender<AgentEvent>` (cloned on each emit)
- `pub struct AgentBuilder { id: Option<AgentId>, system_prompt: Option<String>, models: HashMap<ModelRole, Arc<dyn ARModel>> }`:
  - `pub fn new() -> Self`
  - `pub fn id(mut self, id: AgentId) -> Self`
  - `pub fn system_prompt(mut self, prompt: impl Into<String>) -> Self`
  - `pub fn model(mut self, role: ModelRole, model: Arc<dyn ARModel>) -> Self`
  - `pub fn build(self) -> Result<Agent, Error>` — requires `id`, `system_prompt`, and at least one entry under `ModelRole::Default`. Returns `Error::Configuration(...)` otherwise. The builder does NOT take inbound/outbound channels — those are wired by the Harness when it registers the Agent with the MessageBus. Provide `pub(crate) fn attach(&mut self, inbound, outbound)` or fold the channels into `Agent::run(...)` parameters; pick whichever keeps the type cleaner. Justify the choice in a single-line comment.
- `pub enum Error`:
  - `Configuration(String)`
  - `Model(crate::model::Error)` (via `From`)
  - `Send` (broadcast send when no receivers; treat as non-fatal — log and continue)
  - Manual `Display` + `std::error::Error`.
- `pub async fn run(mut self) -> Result<(), Error>` — the event loop. Pseudocode:
  ```
  while let Some(block) = self.inbound.recv().await {
      let node = self.history.append(block);
      let _ = self.outbound.send(AgentEvent::BlockComplete { block: node });
      let linearized = self.history.linearize();
      let model = self.models.get(&ModelRole::Default).ok_or(Error::Configuration("no default model".into()))?.clone();
      let mut stream = model.complete(&self.system_prompt, &linearized);
      let mut buffer = String::new();
      let mut last_usage = Usage::default();
      while let Some(evt) = stream.next().await {
          match evt {
              Ok(ModelStreamEvent::ContentDelta { text }) => {
                  buffer.push_str(&text);
                  let _ = self.outbound.send(AgentEvent::TokenDelta { text });
              }
              Ok(ModelStreamEvent::Usage(u)) => { last_usage = u; }
              Ok(ModelStreamEvent::MessageComplete { usage }) => { last_usage = usage; }
              Ok(_) => {} // other variants are no-ops for Phase 1
              Err(e) => return Err(Error::Model(e)),
          }
      }
      let agent_msg = Block::AgentMessage { from: self.id, content: buffer, timestamp: SystemTime::now() };
      let node = self.history.append(agent_msg);
      let _ = self.outbound.send(AgentEvent::BlockComplete { block: node });
      let _ = self.outbound.send(AgentEvent::RunComplete { usage: last_usage });
  }
  Ok(())
  ```
  Notes:
  - When `inbound.recv()` returns `None` (all senders dropped), the loop exits cleanly with `Ok(())`. This is the shutdown signal — the Harness drops its inbound senders during `shutdown()`.
  - Broadcast-send failures (`SendError` when no receivers) are non-fatal. Plan.md §"Outbound channel" says the channel is lossy for slow consumers; absent receivers is the extreme case.
  - `buffer` accumulates ContentDelta text. If the upstream emits `ContentComplete { text }`, prefer using that as authoritative for the appended Block content; otherwise fall back to `buffer`. Document the choice in a one-line comment.
  - Do NOT spawn from inside `run`. The Harness spawns one task per Agent and awaits its JoinHandle.

## Harness wiring change
The Step 6 placeholder spawned task must be replaced with `Agent::run(agent).await`. This is the only Step 6 file the Step 7 Bead may modify. Keep the diff minimal:
- Step 6 left a `PendingAgent` placeholder; Step 7 replaces `Harness::start`'s spawn-body with construction of the real `Agent` from the `PendingAgent` (resolve the model from `self.models`) followed by `tokio::spawn(agent.run())`.

## Tests
- `agent_run_processes_one_user_message`: construct a `StubArModel` that yields three `ContentDelta { text }` events followed by `MessageComplete { usage: Usage { input_tokens: 5, output_tokens: 7 } }`; wire an in-memory bus; send one `UserMessage` to the Agent; assert that the broadcast receiver sees three `TokenDelta`s, two `BlockComplete`s (UserMessage then AgentMessage), and one `RunComplete { usage: { 5, 7 } }`, in that order. Bound the test with `tokio::time::timeout(Duration::from_secs(2), ...)`.
- `agent_run_exits_when_inbound_closed`: build an Agent, drop the inbound sender (`MessageBus::send_inbound` side), call `agent.run().await`; assert it returns `Ok(())` within 1s.
- `agent_run_propagates_model_error`: `StubArModel` yields a single `Err(model::Error::Api { status: 500, message: "boom".into() })`; assert `agent.run().await` returns `Err(Error::Model(_))`.

`StubArModel` lives in the test module (or `#[cfg(test)] mod test_support` if reused across test modules).

## Definition of Done
- `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`, `cargo nextest run` all pass.
- No STYLE_GUIDE.md violations.
- No `unwrap`/`expect` outside `#[cfg(test)]`.

## Out of scope
- Skills, tools, ReasoningTrace, ToolCall, ToolResult Block handling beyond pass-through to History
- Adaptive-reasoning model dispatch (the loop only uses `ModelRole::Default`)
- `prepare_for_completion` (the Bead linearizes the head directly; the placeholder lives in plan.md and is deferred)
